│  Content Snippet: ### 1. Foundational Level – The Starting Point                  │
│                                                                                   │
│  For beginners, the AWS Certified Cloud Practitioner is the best starting point.  │
│  This foundational certification is designed for individuals with little or no    │
│  experience in cloud computing. It covers essential concepts like basic cloud     │
│  services, AWS architecture, security, and pricing models.                        │
│                                                                                   │
│  ## Why start with the Cloud Practitioner certification?                          │
│                                                                                   │
│  To prepare for this certification, AWS provides free resources such as           │
│  whitepapers, practice exams, and training sessions.                              │
│                                                                                   │
│  ### 2. Associate Level – Building Technical Skills                               │
│                                                                                   │
│  After the foundational certification, the next step is the Associate level. At   │
│  this stage, you'll need to get hands-on with AWS services and start exploring    │
│  more technical topics.                                                           │
│                                                                                   │
│                                                                                   │
