│  app), create a `Dockerfile` that describes how to build its environment, and     │
│  then build your Docker image.\n2.  **Store your Image in a Registry:** You push  │
│  your Docker image to a container registry (like Amazon ECR, which we'll cover    │
│  next). This makes your image accessible to ECS.\n3.  **Define your Task          │
│  Definition:** You create a Task Definition (our \"recipe\") that points to your  │
│  Docker image in the registry, specifies CPU/memory requirements, port mappings,  │
│  and any environment variables.\n4.  **Create an ECS Cluster:** This is the       │
│  logical grouping of resources where your containers will run. For Fargate, you   │
│  don't manage the underlying servers, but you still need a cluster.\n5.           │
│  **Create an ECS Service:** You then create an ECS Service, telling it:\n    *    │
│  Which Task Definition to use.\n    *   How many copies (tasks) of your           │
