│  incredibly valuable for understanding what your robot did, when it did it, and   │
│  if anything went wrong.\n\n**CloudWatch Logs** are that tiny notebook for your   │
│  applications and AWS resources. Instead of just numbers (metrics), logs capture  │
│  detailed, raw text data about events that happen. This could be:\n*   Error      │
│  messages from your code.\n*   Information about user requests to your            │
│  website.\n*   System messages from your servers.\n*   Any custom messages you    │
│  want your application to record.\n\nCloudWatch Logs provides a centralized       │
│  place to store, monitor, and analyze these log files. Instead of digging         │
│  through individual server files, all your logs are neatly organized and          │
│  searchable in one spot.\n\n**Why is this useful for your hobby project?** When   │
